617. ‘To the solstitial goal of Cancer. ’ There are two solstices in the year, the summer solstice when the sun is nearest the equator in the sign of Cancer, June 22, and the winter when it is furthest away in the sign of Capricorn, December 21. The solstice

received its name from the fact that the sun seemed to stand still when it reached the turning· point.
